description:
The investment seeks to track (before fees and expenses) the price and yield performance of its underlying index, the IQ Enhanced Core Bond U.S. Index.
 The fund is a "fund of funds" which means it invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in the investments included in its underlying index. The underlying index seeks to outperform the U.S. dollar-denominated taxable fixed income universe by using a combination of short- and long-term momentum to overweight and underweight various sectors of the investment grade U.S. fixed income securities market.
